                            <comment id="12762768" author="srs" created="Tue, 6 Oct 2009 20:31:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes. Clearly this is a bug. Servlet spec dictates that getPathInfo should return what&apos;s after servlet-path and before query string parameters.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12762781" author="srs" created="Tue, 6 Oct 2009 21:16:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Added fix for this in trunk. Need a little more testing, but I am pretty sure this will fix getPathinfo() problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12762785" author="srs" created="Tue, 6 Oct 2009 21:23:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Verified with my local installation. Fix is ok.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12762786" author="srs" created="Tue, 6 Oct 2009 21:29:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Actually. Need to check this a little bit more.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12762793" author="srs" created="Tue, 6 Oct 2009 21:41:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Now it seems to be fixed in trunk. Request attributes on URI is not longer returned in getPathInfo().&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
